Title: Cache ticket scan in housekeeping to avoid re-reading unchanged files
Status: open
Created: 2026-04-27
Author: claude

--- log ---
2026-04-27T00:00Z claude created

--- body ---
## Problem

Housekeeping scans all tickets on every run to find expired sweep-skip entries and
update pick-assessments. Climate_finance has ~125 tickets; reading them all costs
$0.30–0.40 alone and grows with the repo.

## Solution

Store a scan manifest in `.claude/sweep-state/hk-scan-cache.json`:
- per-file: `{path, mtime_or_sha, last_scanned}`
- Skip files unchanged since last scan (compare git blob sha or mtime)
- Only re-read tickets modified since last housekeeping commit

Use `git diff --name-only <last-hk-commit> HEAD -- tickets/` to get the changed set.

## Acceptance criteria

- Housekeeping reads ≤ changed tickets + newly-expired sweep-skip on each run
- Cache file committed alongside housekeeping changes
- Regression: still catches all expired sweep-skip entries

## Notes

Synergistic with ticket 0027 (pick-ticket incremental assessment), which uses
the same principle for pick-ticket.
